        <Parent_String>seminaries (buildings) [300386971], religious schools (buildings) [300448956], school buildings by subject [300006525], schools (buildings) [300006495], academic buildings [300444406], institutional buildings [300132384], single built works by function [300004894], single built works by specific type [300004795], single built works (built environment) [300004790], Single Built Works (hierarchy name) [300004789], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Buildings that house educational facilities with higher education curricula specifically designed to train rabbis; for schools providing training in Talmudic law generally, but not necessarily specifically for the rabbinate, use "yeshivas." For schools providing education for the priesthood, use "theological seminaries."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instalación educacional con un elevado programa educativo específicamente diseñado para la enseñanza de los rabinos. Para escuelas que proporcionan instrucción general en las leyes de Talmud, pero no neceseriamente de manera específica para los rabinos, empléese "yeshiva". Para escuelas que proporcionan educación para el sacerdocio, empléese "seminario conciliar".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor onderwijsinstellingen met hogere opleidingsprogramma's die speciaal zijn bedoeld om rabbijnen op te leiden; gebruik 'yeshivas' voor scholen die les geven in de talmoedische wet in het algemeen en niet noodzakelijkerwijs alleen voor het rabbinaat. Gebruik 'theologische hogescholen' voor scholen die een opleiding bieden voor het priesterschap.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>提供高等教育課程以培訓猶太導師拉比的教育場所；而依照塔木德法典加以提供學習課程，但卻不以培養法學博士為唯一目的的學校，稱為「經學院」；提供司鐸教育的學校，則使用「神學院」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gebäude, in dem eine Bildungseinrichtung mit Hochschullehrplan untergebracht ist, der speziell für die Ausbildung von Rabbinern entwickelt wurde; für eine Schule, die eine Ausbildung im talmudischen Recht im Allgemeinen anbietet, aber nicht notwendigerweise speziell auf das Rabbinat zielt, siehe "Jeschiwa". Für eine Schule, die eine Ausbildung für das Priesteramt bietet, siehe "theologische Fakultät".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
